{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, IFEval is a single-turn IF benchmark with verifiable instructions, and MultiChallenge is a multi-turn IF benchmark with diverse instructions and instance-level rubrics.",
    "For AdvancedIF and MultiChallenge, we choose o3-mini as our rubric verifier as the same as in benchmarking SOTA models in Section 3.1.",
    "Following prior work (Zhou et al., 2023), we report the average performance of IFEval in terms of the percentage of responses that satisfy the instructions under both loose and strict evaluation settings.",
    "For MultiChallenge, we report the average score across all instances as the final performance.",
    "For AdvancedIF, we report the percentage of responses that fully satisfy all criteria in the rubric for each category of instructions, including ComplexIF (CIF), Carried Context (CC), and System Steerability (SS)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
